The prion diseases are a group of fatal neurodegenerative diseases that include scrapie in sheep and goats; bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE)1 in cattle; and Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD), Gerstmann-Straussler-Scheinker disease, fatal familial insomnia (FFI), and kuru in humans. The human diseases may be inherited, arise sporadically, or be acquired through exposure to infectious prions
